I think what I like most about CS:GO is how true to the franchise the gameplay itself remains. CS is a timeless classic, and any real changes to it would have been a mistake. Luckily this takes the best part of the game, ( the gameplay), preserves it, cleans things up a little bit, gives us a new matchmaking system, not only that but is now free to play, forever preserving the title and its relevance to old and new gamers alike. I am not necessarily an old- school purist, I do like my modern fps games as well. But to me the strength of CS lies in its simplicity, a place where most modern games really tend to overdo things in my opinion regarding loadouts, specialty weapons, promotional items, pay to win OP weapons etc. This is just pure fps competition distilled to its core. This game saved my life.
I am 42.
My ex-wife and I have a daughter together, and adopted our son together. They are now both 4 years old.
When we were going through our separation, I found myself lost and miserable. I was self destructive. I got so mad one day from everything spiraling out of my control that I punched some concrete in a moment of overwhelming emotion. That caused me to break my 5th metacarpal in my right hand... my working hand... my games hand.. the hand that I held and carried my children to bed with.. The hand I desperately needed to make sure I could continue to provide.
After learning of the severity of my self-inflicted damage, I was borderline suicidal. Keep in mind that just a few months before this, I was the happiest man with no history of depression or anxiety. I have never had fits of rage, or been one to break down and cry, but I was in a low spot that just really buried me from being able to see the light on the other side.
Having nothing better to do, I searched for a game I could play, ONE HANDED while I recovered. I somehow stumbled upon this game and read some of the reviews. I decided that it had to be worth a shot... I must admit, I didn't beat the game, or play nearly as long as some of you. In fact, I may have only played this game a day or two.. With that being said, after doing so, I had a new found joy and hope for life. I was able to put behind me the pain and suffering that had been cast over me. I was able to experience other peoples joy and happiness. I was able to see the fruits of my "labor". I relaxed for 5 ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ minutes to this music long enough to realize that I was going to be okay.
After coming to that realization, I turned the game off, and I went back to work. It hurt my hand like hell but I was motivated. I stopped feeling so damn sorry for myself, and I became the father I needed to be in that moment, not the weak boy I was behaving as.
Today, I am close friend with my kids mother. We don't fight, or argue, or say hurtful things to each other. We are parents, and friends.
I now have 3 kids. My third child is, wait for it, ALSO 4 YEARS OLD. The woman I am with was going through a very similar situation at the time of my own separation, and we just stumbled in to each others life unexpectedly. We have been in a relationship for a year now, and are very happy together.
Moral of the story, you never know what life holds in store for you, and if I would have given up when all the odds were stacked against me, I wouldn't be where I am today. This silly little game helped me realize that.

This game saved my life.
I am 42.
My ex-wife and I have a daughter together, and adopted our son together. They are now both 4 years old.
When we were going through our separation, I found myself lost and miserable. I was self destructive. I got so mad one day from everything spiraling out of my control that I punched some concrete in a moment of overwhelming emotion. That caused me to break my 5th metacarpal in my right hand... my working hand... my games hand.. the hand that I held and carried my children to bed with.. The hand I desperately needed to make sure I could continue to provide.
After learning of the severity of my self-inflicted damage, I was borderline suicidal. Keep in mind that just a few months before this, I was the happiest man with no history of depression or anxiety. I have never had fits of rage, or been one to break down and cry, but I was in a low spot that just really buried me from being able to see the light on the other side.
Having nothing better to do, I searched for a game I could play, ONE HANDED while I recovered. I somehow stumbled upon this game and read some of the reviews. I decided that it had to be worth a shot... I must admit, I didn't beat the game, or play nearly as long as some of you. In fact, I may have only played this game a day or two.. With that being said, after doing so, I had a new found joy and hope for life. I was able to put behind me the pain and suffering that had been cast over me. I was able to experience other peoples joy and happiness. I was able to see the fruits of my "labor". I relaxed for 5 ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ minutes to this music long enough to realize that I was going to be okay.
After coming to that realization, I turned the game off, and I went back to work. It hurt my hand like hell but I was motivated. I stopped feeling so damn sorry for myself, and I became the father I needed to be in that moment, not the weak boy I was behaving as.
Today, I am close friend with my kids mother. We don't fight, or argue, or say hurtful things to each other. We are parents, and friends.
I now have 3 kids. My third child is, wait for it, ALSO 4 YEARS OLD. The woman I am with was going through a very similar situation at the time of my own separation, and we just stumbled in to each others life unexpectedly. We have been in a relationship for a year now, and are very happy together.
Moral of the story, you never know what life holds in store for you, and if I would have given up when all the odds were stacked against me, I wouldn't be where I am today. This silly little game helped me realize that.

Counter-Strike: Global Offensive (csgo) is a very unique game even 9 years after it's release
lets first talk about the gameplay, the gunplay is simple, fast, smooth and responsive, while most modern games have aiming down sights and sprawling arenas csgo has stayed with it's classic roots but it manages to do that while still feeling modern, the game is easy to learn but very hard to master and despite how simple it may look at first glance this game gets complex when you have to remember smoke grenade line ups and other similar crucial aspects of the game
the second point that i wish to make is the optimisation/graphics, csgo has acceptable graphics but they're not great when compared to most modern games although that's acceptable because of how well optimised the game is since it's graphics are dated, even running csgo at 4k is not a challenge for most modern PCs
the third and final point is the community, csgo has a rather special community which mostly cares about how much money you've wasted on skins rather then your actual skill and there are plenty of hackers that are happy to ruin you day, the solo queuing experience is a bit of a mess because you either get really good teammates that communicate and guide you to victory or you get toxic Russian kids that don't even know how to shoot, csgo contains a main 5v5 competitive mode and a 2v2 competitive mode so you can avoid the toxic lobbies by just playing 2v2 with a friend but sadly I've only ever experianced solo queuing
in conclusion csgo is a very good game that's worth checking out, it's even free so there's nothing to lose but if you really want to get the full experience you have to either purchase prime or grind deathmatch until you unlock prime status because non-prime matchmaking is just filled with hackers in every match

I've been playing Counter Strike casually on and off for nearly 2 decades now. Its obviously something that works well with what it has, but there are some core design flaws that havent aged well, especially since this game is still being updated and self-awarded a "labor of love award", which is fine, Im sure they worked hard on what they did, because again, it works.
So, pros:
- Top tier old school gunplay
- Great competitive game modes, some game modes being more unforgiving/challenging than others
- Decent gun variety
- New content still being created to this day
- Game is now free
- Bots allow you to practice maps without pressure
Cons:
- Some basic mechanics that would probably change the entire "feel" of counter-strike which are commonplace nowadays remain a glaring indication of how much this has aged. Its still fun, but the fact that I cant hit someones face with the butt of my gun alway strikes me as odd. As well as things like sprinting, which I'd think trained operatives could do. Instead, the button usually associated to sprinting is the one linked to walking. It just simply kill the immersion when there are no burst of speed mechanics, or explosive movements that any trained human can do, like sprinting, lunging, climbing, or even things like tilting your head around corners. These are things humans can do, but not the characters in CS:GO apparently. They just walk around hopping like iron ankled robots, incapable of bending their spines until they die, at which point the rag dolls somehow feel less stiff and artifical than the actual mobility options available to the player. That being said, I dont expect such things to change.
- Okay this one is just the most annoying thing that is the bane of FPS games.. The ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ spawning in Team Death match is absolute, utter garbage. I cant even understand how this is in a game, at all. The amount of times where players have spawned directly behind me, sometimes 2-3-4 of them, and just completely destroyed me without my knowing they were there is just frustrating. Its not "tactical" to have to predict people will spawn behind you, or worse, literally under you. It doesnt make sense. Its been decades, and its still atrociously bad. Its still the worst part of the game. At this point I dont expect valve to fix this, but they really, really should. It would make their game infinitely less frustrating. Just make people spawn not where their enemies can kill them, or be killed by them. Im sure they can program this. Ive seen it in many other games.
- Shotguns are pretty arse, although they kill at close range, the drop off is absurd. The amount of times I shot someone at 5 meters away, only to see I hit them 4 times for 23 damage is silly. It doesnt make sense. Thats not how shotguns work.
- Bots are hit or miss, they feel like sometimes aim perfectly constantly, or they are bumbling automated walking targets
- You need to pay to open the loot you win from playing the game.. So they hang skins in front of you, and tell you to buy a key to get it. Sort of a weird choice, but Im sure it makes them tonnes of cash
- Pretty toxic community at times. Also, a lot of young kids seem to play this. The worst is the occasional hacker.
TL;DR
Good free game, but rapidly aging. Maybe time for an overhaul

It's hard to believe but Cs 1.6 was better optimized, had less hackers and a better overall community.
Cs:go has loading issues, doesn't matter your specs, it will take most people 30-120 seconds to load any map every single time you join a match, wich gives an advantage to people who take 5-20 seconds, there are some "tricks" to improve the overall loading but it doesn't always work.
It has decent graphics, wich still work in low spec computers with good fps, servers usually work well, just sometimes have issues, 50,000 players looking for a match and it suddenly takes over 20 minutes and don't find one, restarting the game usually fix it though.
The game kind of expect players to hack, you have a few report options only, can't even write anything on the report, and most of the options are related to cheating, "wall hack", "aim hack", "other hack", feel like they simple don't care since it's easier for them and they will still receive money.
You can get 1-2 cases and skins per week, and some players simple do anything for those, there are many abusing the drop system to farm the items and sell at the steam market for easy money. And that's it, for many players this is a drop simulator while devs get more and more money adding useless stuff instead of fixing the game.
Community is toxic, but let's be honest, you switch a single setting to off and you will never hear them and will still play the game normally. May not help in competitive since you need teamwork but... Still better than listening to this community. You can also look for a custom server with a decent community, it's hard to find but not impossible.
Feel like most modes were rushed, hitboxes have a small delay, accuracy is messed up, it's still fun though. Many of the classic maps are still there, the weapons and gear too, other than better graphics, few new maps and modes, no big changes since 1.6. The "new" stuff is usually new skins or other methods to grab your cash.
The matches rely on luck, you may find a match where the enemy team is way better than yours or cheat to win, or you can also join a match where you won't even try at all and will win easily.
It's still fun if you have someone to play with or if you wanna kill some time, it's now free and worth a shot, you can also create and manage your own server easily, so with some work you can actually have a nice time playing it.

I started playing counter strike with the very first version of the game CS 1.6, an old one, but still popular. Often with friends went to computer clubs to shoot with each other. Since then, CS Source has already been released, and in 2012 Global Offensive was released, and for 8 years it has been ranked first online on the Steam gaming platform.
The essence of the game is extremely simple. Choose one of the teams - Special Forces or Terrorists, and kill people from the enemy team. At the same time, you can win in other ways, depending on the cards, for example, there are cards on which terrorists must put a bomb, and special forces must clear it. Or one should guard the hostages, and the other should take them out of the building. Also, Global Offensive has added many new game modes, such as battle royale. There are also cases that contain very beautiful weapon skins. And the most important thing is that there is no donat in the game, everything is decided by the skill. I spent many hours in it, and the game itself does not get bored. Sometimes you get on cheaters, but if you play leagues, then there are practically no cheaters. And remember, if a person plays better than you-it does not mean that he has CHEATS.
Let's summarize.
Pros: New maps; new modes, operations (For the sake of truth, they come out very rarely); dedicated servers (with different mods and additions); beautiful skins; exciting gameplay.
Cons: Poor anti-cheat; boosters; inadequate personalities; stacks of 3-4 people when playing solo; official servers on poor 64 tickrate
